The paper proposes an adaptive repair method using evolutionary computation to solve a complex constrained optimization problem in power system operations. This involves the optimization of multiple parameters and constraints, which suggests a strong connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of evolutionary computation also suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper provides a guideline for constraint handling, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
